WEBVTT

00:01.752 --> 00:03.795
<i>[singer vocalizing]</i>

00:03.795 --> 00:05.839
I'm really enjoying
my vacation.

00:05.839 --> 00:08.175
[laughter]

00:08.175 --> 00:11.929
Who was that cutie
you were talking to?

00:11.929 --> 00:13.555
<i>ALISON:
Tonight is my last night.</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:15.474
I was hoping
we could do something special.

00:16.892 --> 00:18.477
<i>CLAIRE: Mama?</i>

00:18.477 --> 00:19.978
What is it, sweetie?

00:19.978 --> 00:22.064
Alison didn't
come home last night.

00:24.691 --> 00:27.110
<i>DETECTIVE:
Multiple witnesses saw Alison</i>

00:27.110 --> 00:31.240
<i>at the bar last night
with two young, local men.</i>

00:31.240 --> 00:35.494
<i>We have determined
the death of Alison Thomas...</i>

00:35.494 --> 00:37.162
was an accident.

00:37.162 --> 00:38.872
But this was not an accident.

00:38.872 --> 00:40.666
<i>And everyone knows it.</i>

00:42.793 --> 00:45.712
<i>CLAIRE: My sister's murder
was headline news for years.</i>

00:46.880 --> 00:48.257
<i>Sometimes it feels like</i>

00:48.257 --> 00:50.467
<i>the whole world knows
more than I do.</i>

00:50.467 --> 00:51.843
<i>SUNITA: You need
to get some help,</i>

00:51.843 --> 00:53.887
because at this point,
you've become a stalker.

00:57.474 --> 01:00.394
<i>CLAIRE:
I need to keep doing this.</i>

01:00.394 --> 01:02.771
<i>For her.</i>

01:09.194 --> 01:11.780
[footsteps running,
person panting]

01:11.780 --> 01:14.408
<i>[ominous music]</i>

01:14.408 --> 01:17.202
<i>CLAIRE: Alison didn't
come home last night.</i>

01:17.202 --> 01:24.167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:26.628 --> 01:28.672
[loud crack]
PERSON: Gogo!

01:28.672 --> 01:30.924
PERSON: Malcolm!

01:30.924 --> 01:33.927
[thunder booming]

01:33.927 --> 01:40.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:40.934 --> 01:42.728
PERSON: Alison!

01:44.062 --> 01:45.314
PERSON 2: Can you hear me?

01:45.314 --> 01:48.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:48.108 --> 01:52.070
PERSON 3: Hey! Alison!
PERSON 4: Alison!

01:52.070 --> 01:55.073
[distant indistinct shouting]

01:55.073 --> 02:01.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:01.079 --> 02:04.082
[siren blaring]

02:08.378 --> 02:11.381
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:11.381 --> 02:17.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:17.512 --> 02:20.098
Oh, God, I'm sorry. Please.

02:20.098 --> 02:22.726
I'm so sorry.
[panting]

02:22.726 --> 02:26.772
Our Father, who art in Heaven,
hallowed be Thy name.

02:26.772 --> 02:28.357
Thy kingdom come.
[indistinct chatter]

02:28.357 --> 02:31.068
Thy will be done on Earth
as it is in Heaven.

02:31.068 --> 02:32.944
Give us this day
our daily bread,

02:32.944 --> 02:35.739
and forgive us our trespasses
as we forgive those...

02:35.739 --> 02:42.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:01.348 --> 03:04.434
<i>[eerie music]</i>

03:04.434 --> 03:11.483
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:14.027 --> 03:17.030
<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

03:17.030 --> 03:24.037
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:25.414 --> 03:28.208
[clears throat]

03:28.208 --> 03:31.461
Can I buy you a drink?

03:31.461 --> 03:34.631
I mean, sure.
I like free things.

03:34.631 --> 03:36.299
What'll you have?

03:36.299 --> 03:38.593
Uh, can I have another one
of these masterpieces, please?

03:38.593 --> 03:41.346
And he'll have one, too.
BARTENDER: You got it.

03:41.346 --> 03:43.181
I'm Emily.

03:43.181 --> 03:45.100
Trev.

03:45.100 --> 03:47.394
And, uh, what do you do, Emily?

03:47.394 --> 03:50.230
I'm an editor--environmental
documentaries, mostly.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.941
Ah, a do-gooder.

03:52.941 --> 03:55.026
- Sometimes.
- [chuckles]

03:55.026 --> 03:58.572
And let me guess--
you're a consultant?

03:58.572 --> 04:01.158
I mean, the suit,
the bespoke tie at half-mast

04:01.158 --> 04:04.870
mourning the end of another
satisfying day consulting.

04:04.870 --> 04:07.956
Plus, the Brecht Consulting bag
kind of gave it away.

04:07.956 --> 04:11.042
I see.
You think I'm a total douche.

04:11.042 --> 04:12.669
No, not at all.

04:12.669 --> 04:14.796
Good people can work
at problematic companies.

04:14.796 --> 04:16.548
You know, change from within
and whatnot.

04:16.548 --> 04:18.592
Josh, over here.

04:18.592 --> 04:19.968
Did we make
a new friend again?

04:19.968 --> 04:21.887
This is Trev.

04:21.887 --> 04:23.180
He works at Brecht,

04:23.180 --> 04:24.848
but he's pretty sure
he's one of the good ones.

04:24.848 --> 04:26.224
- JOSH: Oh.
- This is my boyfriend, Josh.

04:26.224 --> 04:27.601
He's a civil rights lawyer,

04:27.601 --> 04:29.644
so he's definitely
one of the good ones.

04:29.644 --> 04:31.271
Watch out for that one.

04:31.271 --> 04:33.690
Yes.
Beware of women with opinions.

04:33.690 --> 04:36.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:36.902 --> 04:38.737
Should we go home
and rechristen our apartment?

04:38.737 --> 04:41.573
I'd love to, but I got to
get back to the office.

04:41.573 --> 04:43.658
- No.
- Why don't I walk you home?

04:43.658 --> 04:46.453
I mean, I thought you said
Flatbush was totally safe.

04:46.453 --> 04:48.121
All right, you caught me.
I still worry.

04:48.121 --> 04:49.915
Well, I'll be fine.

04:49.915 --> 04:51.416
- JOSH: Mm-hmm?
- Mm-hmm.

04:51.416 --> 04:52.876
Okay.

04:52.876 --> 04:55.879
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

04:55.879 --> 05:00.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:00.717 --> 05:02.511
PERSON:
Ooh, I see you looking, mama.

05:02.511 --> 05:03.762
Come on. Come on.

05:03.762 --> 05:06.056
You know you want some of this.
Come on.

05:06.056 --> 05:09.059
[person continues speaking
indistinctly]

05:09.059 --> 05:16.107
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:23.323 --> 05:26.326
<i>["Everything's Coming Up Love"
playing]</i>

05:26.326 --> 05:30.914
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:30.914 --> 05:33.917
[plane engine thrumming]

05:33.917 --> 05:35.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:35.335 --> 05:39.631
SINGERS: ♪ Love is a flower
that blooms ♪

05:39.631 --> 05:42.133
SINGER:
♪ In the springtime ♪

05:42.133 --> 05:45.387
SINGERS:
♪ In the springtime ♪

05:45.387 --> 05:49.432
♪ Beneath the light
of the moon ♪

05:49.432 --> 05:51.893
SINGER:
♪ In the springtime ♪

05:51.893 --> 05:53.311
SINGERS:
♪ In the springtime ♪

05:53.311 --> 05:55.021
CHILD: He started it!

05:55.021 --> 05:58.525
PERSON: See, their sister's
being naughty.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.860
BRETT: 200 bucks
for shuttle service.

06:00.860 --> 06:02.362
I mean, is it too much to ask

06:02.362 --> 06:04.030
for it to be here
when we arrive?

06:04.030 --> 06:06.408
It's like that everywhere
in the Caribbean.

06:06.408 --> 06:09.411
- Island time, they call it.
- Oh, my God, Dad.

06:09.411 --> 06:10.745
MIA: Darien is lovely.

06:10.745 --> 06:12.289
We considered that
when we were leaving the city.

06:12.289 --> 06:13.456
We're in White Plains.

06:13.456 --> 06:15.292
JAMIE:
Oh. And those are your girls?

06:15.292 --> 06:17.711
Yes. This is Alison.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.713
She's on break from college.

06:19.713 --> 06:20.755
Freshman at Princeton.

06:20.755 --> 06:22.257
Princeton?
MIA: Yeah.

06:22.257 --> 06:24.134
Good for you.
BILL: And she's a superstar--

06:24.134 --> 06:25.886
swim team, tennis team,

06:25.886 --> 06:28.179
graduated high school
second in her class.

06:28.179 --> 06:30.807
Plus, I have a completely
overblown sense of self-worth

06:30.807 --> 06:34.060
due to my
incredibly doting parents.

06:34.060 --> 06:36.271
And how old are you, sweetheart?

06:36.271 --> 06:38.398
It's okay.
This is Clairey.

06:38.398 --> 06:40.066
She's seven.

06:40.066 --> 06:41.818
She's a little bit shy.

06:41.818 --> 06:43.486
I wish ours
could be more shy.

06:43.486 --> 06:44.654
I'm not the one who fed them

06:44.654 --> 06:46.823
two packs of candy
on the plane, Brett.

06:48.825 --> 06:50.660
Oh, great!
[overlapping chatter]

06:50.660 --> 06:53.204
I guess we'll see you there.

06:53.204 --> 06:55.415
[indistinct chatter]

06:55.415 --> 07:02.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:13.767 --> 07:16.811
MIA:
I spy with my little eye

07:16.811 --> 07:19.481
something blue.

07:19.481 --> 07:21.983
The sky.
Too easy, Mama.

07:21.983 --> 07:26.029
Ah. I spy...

07:26.029 --> 07:28.865
something with feathers.

07:28.865 --> 07:30.659
Clairey, no, remember
what we talked about?

07:30.659 --> 07:32.869
No arm writing.
You spell it in your mind.

07:32.869 --> 07:34.454
Mom, leave her alone.

07:34.454 --> 07:37.082
DRIVER:
[muttering indistinctly]

07:37.082 --> 07:40.043
[horns honking]

07:43.046 --> 07:44.714
[engine sputtering]

07:44.714 --> 07:47.676
I spy a girl.

07:49.135 --> 07:50.512
Why'd she do that?

07:50.512 --> 07:52.347
Clairey, did you know
that 2 billion people,

07:52.347 --> 07:54.849
which is more than a third
of humans on Earth,

07:54.849 --> 07:56.434
live on less than $2 a day?

07:56.434 --> 07:57.560
She's seven, Al.

07:57.560 --> 07:58.853
Does she really need
to know that?

07:58.853 --> 08:00.689
I don't think seven's
too young to learn

08:00.689 --> 08:02.857
about the hypocrisy
of our lifestyle.

08:02.857 --> 08:04.317
I'm warning you. Enough.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.694
ALISON:
Hypocrisy, Clairey,

08:05.694 --> 08:08.029
is when you say
you feel a certain way,

08:08.029 --> 08:10.323
but your actions
directly contradict that.

08:10.323 --> 08:12.867
Kind of like how Mom and Dad
say they care about poverty,

08:12.867 --> 08:14.828
but instead of doing
anything about it,

08:14.828 --> 08:17.122
they plan a luxury vacation
on an island

08:17.122 --> 08:19.541
where people don't even have
solid roofs over their heads.

08:19.541 --> 08:20.959
Alison...

08:20.959 --> 08:22.627
DRIVER:
Miss, on our island,

08:22.627 --> 08:23.962
the people
are well fed and happy.

08:23.962 --> 08:25.338
MIA:
You have to excuse my daughter.

08:25.338 --> 08:27.006
She's in her first year
of college

08:27.006 --> 08:29.884
and reading
a bunch of Toni Morrison.

08:29.884 --> 08:32.887
Her heart's in the right place.
She's just...

08:32.887 --> 08:35.223
a little confused.

08:35.223 --> 08:38.226
<i>[upbeat tropical music]</i>

08:38.226 --> 08:45.275
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:51.781 --> 08:54.325
PERSON: <i>Bonjour.</i>
Welcome, welcome.

08:54.325 --> 08:56.745
EDWIN: Hello.

08:56.745 --> 08:58.538
Oh, my God.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.539
Careful.

08:59.539 --> 09:01.166
EDWIN: Welcome.

09:01.166 --> 09:04.502
Welcome to Indigo Bay.

09:04.502 --> 09:06.337
Hello.

09:06.337 --> 09:09.257
- I want to stay another week.
- [laughs]

09:09.257 --> 09:10.925
Thanks. This is beautiful.

09:10.925 --> 09:14.012
The punch is made
with fresh guava, miss.

09:14.012 --> 09:15.972
Trust me, you'll like it.

09:15.972 --> 09:19.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.809 --> 09:21.811
Please go relax.

09:21.811 --> 09:23.938
You must not miss the sunset.

09:23.938 --> 09:25.398
I shall take care of your bags

09:25.398 --> 09:27.650
and see that you are
all checked in.

09:27.650 --> 09:29.903
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:29.903 --> 09:31.488
- There's a pool.
- I know.

09:31.488 --> 09:32.530
You want to go look?

09:32.530 --> 09:34.407
Okay. Have a good one.
Thank you.

09:34.407 --> 09:36.910
Yes. My big man, Gogo.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.411
How's it hanging, boy?

09:38.411 --> 09:40.080
Guess who just got
a $20 tip.

09:40.080 --> 09:41.998
You're shitting me.
From who?

09:41.998 --> 09:44.084
Those anti-men
I took to their room.

09:44.084 --> 09:45.460
He did not even look
at the bill.

09:45.460 --> 09:47.045
He just want to get down
to doing the nasty

09:47.045 --> 09:48.546
with he husband, I guess.

09:48.546 --> 09:52.759
Oh, man, we love
them American anti-men.

09:52.759 --> 09:54.928
Mm.
What are you doing tonight?

09:54.928 --> 09:56.513
Damian's got
that football game.

09:56.513 --> 09:57.639
I cannot tonight.
Don't start.

09:57.639 --> 09:59.182
We can't all be free
and easy, Edwin.

09:59.182 --> 10:01.684
EDWIN: Yeah, by choice, Goges.
By choice, man.

10:01.684 --> 10:04.687
<i>[soft music]</i>

10:04.687 --> 10:10.318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:10.318 --> 10:12.570
[birds chirping]

10:12.570 --> 10:16.032
I spy cotton candy.

10:16.032 --> 10:17.909
[laughs]
That's a good one, Clairey.

10:17.909 --> 10:19.911
BILL: [laughing]

10:19.911 --> 10:23.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:23.248 --> 10:24.833
Look,
there's the kids' club.

10:24.833 --> 10:26.000
Hi.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.711
Come on, Alison,
smell that ocean breeze.

10:28.711 --> 10:30.213
Smell it. [inhales deeply]
[Mia chuckles]

10:30.213 --> 10:32.215
Ahh.

10:32.215 --> 10:35.260
Admit that this resort
is incredible.

10:35.260 --> 10:36.886
Admit that you'd rather be
in paradise

10:36.886 --> 10:38.138
than fucking New Jersey.

10:38.138 --> 10:39.264
And admit--[laughs]

10:39.264 --> 10:40.849
Admit that it's not so awful

10:40.849 --> 10:42.600
to be with your capitalist,

10:42.600 --> 10:44.394
- bougie parents for a week.

10:44.394 --> 10:45.937
- Fine.
- Come on.

10:45.937 --> 10:47.939
It's great.

10:47.939 --> 10:50.483
I'm happy to be here.

10:50.483 --> 10:55.071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:55.071 --> 10:57.073
BILL:
Steph Curry's on a tear.

10:57.073 --> 10:59.659
Warriors are gonna win
another ring this year.

10:59.659 --> 11:02.662
[indistinct chatter]

11:02.662 --> 11:04.873
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:04.873 --> 11:06.291
CHILD: Cookie!

11:06.291 --> 11:08.251
Well, hello.

11:08.251 --> 11:09.419
Hi.

11:09.419 --> 11:11.296
Oh, you have a cookie.

11:11.296 --> 11:13.673
Thank you so much. Oh.

11:13.673 --> 11:14.924
She loves sharing
her cookies.

11:14.924 --> 11:18.636
Oh, well that is wonderful.
Thank you.

11:18.636 --> 11:20.263
- Say "you're welcome."
- You're welcome.

11:20.263 --> 11:23.308
You're so good with her.
You have kids?

11:23.308 --> 11:24.893
Yes.
DAD: Yeah?

11:24.893 --> 11:27.729
Yes. We have a daughter.
DAD: Nice.

11:27.729 --> 11:31.190
Say "goodbye."
BOTH: Bye.

11:31.190 --> 11:32.317
JOSH: Peanut punch?
EMILY: No.

11:32.317 --> 11:33.526
JOSH: I think we need it.
EMILY: No.

11:33.526 --> 11:34.986
We're not getting that.

11:34.986 --> 11:36.696
JOSH: Good source of protein.
Good source of calcium.

11:36.696 --> 11:38.907
Oh. Hey.

11:38.907 --> 11:40.783
Hey, have you seen
that old man in the building,

11:40.783 --> 11:43.953
wears the NASCAR hat
with the little dog?

11:43.953 --> 11:46.039
Oh, Jefe?
That dog's an asshole.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.457
Yeah, right?

11:47.457 --> 11:48.917
Never met
an asshole dog before.

11:48.917 --> 11:49.918
Thanks, man.
EMILY: Thank you.

11:49.918 --> 11:51.002
JOSH: All right.
Have a good one.

11:51.002 --> 11:52.420
EMILY:
Yeah, I want him to like us.

11:52.420 --> 11:54.088
JOSH: Maybe we should buy him
some treats or something.

11:54.088 --> 11:56.466
Bribe him into loving us.
I'm determined to win him over.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.261
- Emily, you okay?
- Yeah.

12:00.261 --> 12:02.805
Yeah, I just haven't seen
that soda since the island.

12:02.805 --> 12:03.973
Yeah, no shit.
So are you okay?

12:03.973 --> 12:05.975
Yeah, I'm fine.
It was just a memory.

12:08.686 --> 12:10.438
JOSH: I know you said
you'd be fine here,

12:10.438 --> 12:12.148
but if it's too much,
we can move somewhere else.

12:12.148 --> 12:13.483
I just want you to feel safe--

12:13.483 --> 12:16.110
Josh, stop.
I'm not freaking out, okay?

12:16.110 --> 12:18.279
It was a memory, a good memory.

12:18.279 --> 12:20.365
That's soda's delish.

12:22.158 --> 12:23.284
Stop.

12:23.284 --> 12:25.745
- Well--
- I would tell you. I promise.

12:25.745 --> 12:27.956
Look, I love Flatbush.
I love our apartment.

12:27.956 --> 12:31.167
[dog barking]
I even love this asshole dog.

12:31.167 --> 12:32.835
JOSH: Hello.

12:32.835 --> 12:35.755
[both laughing]

12:35.755 --> 12:38.758
[distant siren wailing]

12:45.723 --> 12:48.726
<i>[tropical music]</i>

12:48.726 --> 12:53.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:53.982 --> 12:56.317
This is so nice.

12:56.317 --> 12:58.361
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:58.361 --> 13:00.905
Mama...
MIA: Yeah, Clairey?

13:00.905 --> 13:02.407
Where's Alison?

13:02.407 --> 13:04.993
Can you go check
and make sure she's okay?

13:04.993 --> 13:06.703
MIA: Sweetie,
I know you're so excited

13:06.703 --> 13:10.581
to play with your sister,
but teenagers like to sleep in.

13:10.581 --> 13:14.002
Can I get a tour
of your sandcastle?

13:14.002 --> 13:15.169
Yeah?

13:15.169 --> 13:17.505
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:17.505 --> 13:18.965
Wow.

13:20.174 --> 13:21.718
That's the moat.

13:21.718 --> 13:24.304
That's the tower where
the princess lives all alone.

13:24.304 --> 13:25.888
BILL: Alone? Why?

13:25.888 --> 13:28.516
Her parents went to a party
and left her with a babysitter.

13:28.516 --> 13:31.436
She was witch,
so the princess killed her.

13:33.730 --> 13:36.149
Fantastic.

13:36.149 --> 13:38.067
You keep on...

13:40.111 --> 13:41.654
MIA:
I know. I know. I saw it.

13:41.654 --> 13:44.699
We're working on it, okay?
Honey, it's a process.

13:44.699 --> 13:46.868
You don't stop something
like that overnight, right?

13:46.868 --> 13:48.870
People are looking at her.

13:48.870 --> 13:50.329
MIA: No, they're not.

13:50.329 --> 13:53.374
DANA: Interesting how different
she is from her sister.

13:53.374 --> 13:55.209
What sister?

13:55.209 --> 13:56.419
Come on.

13:56.419 --> 13:58.796
You didn't notice
the sumptuous 18-year-old

13:58.796 --> 14:00.423
at dinner last night?

14:02.633 --> 14:04.635
I only have eyes
for you, dear.

14:06.220 --> 14:08.431
And in general,
I don't ogle children.

14:09.640 --> 14:11.434
Sorry.
It's these hormones.

14:11.434 --> 14:12.894
They're making me crazy.

14:12.894 --> 14:14.395
EDWIN: Look at our island,

14:14.395 --> 14:17.899
pulling out
she most beautiful day for you.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.734
What can I be getting you
this morning?

14:19.734 --> 14:21.069
Nothing for me, thanks.

14:21.069 --> 14:23.154
ETHAN: Yeah, I'll get
another, uh, rum punch.

14:23.154 --> 14:24.906
Uh, but do me a favor
and tell your, uh--

14:24.906 --> 14:27.366
tell your bros not to water
it down this time, okay?

